The paper deals with adversarial perturbations in images, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the importance of explainable AI, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the effectiveness of detecting adversarial perturbations, which is related to computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates its approach on standard benchmarks, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
